The '''A5112''' is a road in [[Shropshire]], [[England]] that runs north-south through the town of [[Shrewsbury]]. It runs around the town centre, to the east, and acts as a quicker route through the town than going via the town centre.

Starting north at [[Battlefield, Shropshire|Battlefield]] Island where it joins the [[A49 road|A49]] {{nowrap|({{coord|52.7461|-2.7182|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A5112 road (northern end)}}),}} it consists of Battlefield Road, Whitchurch Road, Telford Way, Robertsford Way, Bage Way, Pritchard Way, Hazeldine Way and Hereford Road. The junctions along it are [[Battlefield, Shropshire|Battlefield]] Roundabout, Battlefield Road Crossroads, [[Harlescott]] Crossroads, [[Heathgates]] Roundabout, Telford Way Roundabout, Crowmere Roundabout, Rea Brook Roundabout, Sutton Park Roundabout, [[Meole Brace]] Island, Hereford Road Roundabout and "Baileys" Roundabout where it rejoins the [[A49 road|A49]], as well as the [[A5 road (Great Britain)|A5]] {{nowrap|({{coord|52.6825|-2.7586|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A5112 road (southern end)}}).}}

The road has a speed limit of {{convert|50|mph|abbr=on}} between [[Meole Brace]] Island and the Telford Way Roundabout with a {{convert|40|mph|abbr=on}} speed limit between the Telford Way Roundabout and the Heathgates Roundabout, and a {{convert|30|mph|abbr=on}} speed limit for the remainder of the route. The road crosses the [[River Severn]] on Telford Way Bridge and is a safe route during flooding of the river.

The road was for a short time in the late 80's and early 90's the [[A49 road|A49]], which now runs around a bypass of the town.

