The '''A586''' is a road in [[England]], which runs from [[Garstang]] to [[Blackpool]], in [[Lancashire]]. 

The road runs a total distance of {{convert|13|mi}}, in a roughly east-west direction, and is both urban and rural in character.  It begins near [[Churchtown, Lancashire|Churchtown]] {{nowrap|({{coord|53.8813|-2.7804|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A586 road (eastern end)}}),}} south of [[Garstang]] and just east of [[Catterall]], as a junction on the [[A6 road (Great Britain)|A6]] Preston Lancaster New Road, immediately to the north of Kirkland Bridge. It runs as a winding rural single-lane road {{convert|2|mi}} south west to [[St Michael's on Wyre]], where it crosses the [[River Wyre]].  Becoming Garstang Road, it runs west, bypassing [[Great Eccleston]] and [[Little Eccleston]], and sharing with the [[A585 road|A585]] as Garstang New Road between [[Larbreck]] and Little [[Singleton, Lancashire|Singleton]], about {{convert|4|mi}} past [[St Michael's On Wyre]].  This is a wider, straighter stretch of road.  The road splits from the A585 after approximately {{convert|1|mi}}, at the Five Lane Ends in Little [[Singleton, Lancashire|Singleton]], and enters the outskirts of [[Poulton-le-Fylde]] as Garstang Road East.  From here, the road becomes progressively more urban. After {{convert|3.5|mi}}, as Poulton Road it crosses the [[A587 road|A587]] at the Plymouth Road [[roundabout]], and becomes Westcliffe Drive as it passes through [[Layton, Lancashire|Layton]], and Talbot Road shortly after. The road continues as Talbot Road past [[Blackpool North railway station]], and passes through the town centre [[one-way system]], eventually terminating at Talbot Square {{nowrap|({{coord|53.8188|-3.0558|type:landmark_region:GB|display=inline|name=A586 road (western end)}}),}} where it meets the [[A584 road|A584]] and [[A583 road|A583]] next to the [[North Pier, Blackpool|North Pier]]. 

