{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Anibare | settlement_type = [[Districts of Nauru|District]] | image_skyline = Nauru(32).jpg | imagesize = 250px | image_caption = Anibare Harbour | image_flag = | image_shield = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = Anibare in Nauru.svg | mapsize = | map_caption = Anibare District within Nauru | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{NRU}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Constituencies of Nauru|Constituency]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Anabar Constituency|Anabar]] | established_title = | established_date = | established_title1 = <!--City rights--> | established_date1 = | leader_title = | leader_name = | area_magnitude = | area_total_km2 = 3.1 | area_land_km2 = | area_water_km2 = | population_as_of = 2011 | population_note = | population_total = 226 | population_footnotes = | population_metro = | population_density_km2 = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_map1 = | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_map_caption1 = | pushpin_mapsize = | coordinates = {{coord|0|31|50|S|166|56|40|E|type:adm1st|display=inline,title}} | timezone = ([[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]]) | utc_offset = | elevation_m = 30 | postal_code_type = [[Postal code]]| | postal_code = | area_code = [[Telephone numbers in Nauru|+674]] | blank_info = | blank1_info = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Anibare''' is a [[district]] in the [[island nation]] [[Nauru]], a part of the [[Anabar Constituency]].
==Geography== It is located in the east of the island, and covers an area of {{convert|3.1|km²|0|abbr=on}}. It has a population of about 250. It is thus Nauru's largest district in area, and among the smallest in population. Nauru's reputation for being densely populated is thus somewhat nuanced, since it refers principally to the average areas and populations of districts other than Anibare.
==Local features== * [[Anibare Bay]]. A beach with white coral sand near the Menen Hotel which is considered the best place on the island to surf or to swim. It also contains the Anibare Harbor, an artificial commercial fishing area. * A [[Phosphate]] stockpile is located in western Anibare.
==See also== * [[Geography of Nauru]] * [[List of settlements in Nauru]] * [[Rail transport in Nauru]]
