{{advert|date=May 2018}} {{primary sources|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox software | name = Google My Maps | logo = Google My Maps Icon.png | screenshot = Google My Maps Civil War Example.png | caption = An example of a map in Google My Maps | author = | developer = [[Google]] | released = {{Start date and age|2007|04|05}} | latest release version = | latest release date = | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | programming language = | platform = | operating system =[[Web application|Web]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | language count = | language footnote = | genre = {{Plainlist | *[[Web mapping]] *[[Vector graphics editor]] *[[Collaborative software]] }} | website = {{URL|https://mymaps.google.com/}} }}
'''Google My Maps''' is a service launched by Google in April 2007 that enables users to create custom maps for personal use or sharing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Introducing My Maps – News announcements – News from Google – Google|url=http://googlepress.blogspot.com/2007/04/introducing-my-maps_05.html|website=googlepress.blogspot.com|accessdate=1 May 2018|language=en}}</ref> Users can add points, lines, and shapes on top of Google Maps, using a [[WYSIWYG]] editor.<ref>{{cite web|title=Introduction to Google My Maps - Computer - My Maps Help|url=https://support.google.com/mymaps/answer/3024396|website=support.google.com|accessdate=1 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>
In November 2014, a new version was released, and maps from the original version were automatically upgraded.<ref>{{cite web|title=Google Groups|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!topic/maps/WtVqu3yCpa4%5B1-25%5D|website=productforums.google.com|accessdate=1 May 2018}}</ref> You can also have layers and customise the items in each layer with uniform styles and having labels for the name or description. There are many different objects you can have as your points, such as the town point, train point, bus point, hospital point or a school points. You can change the colour of anything and change the thickness as well.
