{{Expand Spanish|Ngeremasch|date=March 2017}}
{{unreferenced|date=February 2017}}
'''Ngeremasch''' (also spelled Ngaramasch) is a [[village]] in [[Palau]], and the capital of the [[States of Palau|state]] of [[Angaur]]. Ngaramasch is located west of the runway of Angaur, there are also ferries that connect Angaur to [[Koror]]. The population in 2009 was 135. The village was formerly known as '''Saipan Town'''.

